  "prompt": "How do I save an answer on Quora?",
  "response": "Saving an answer on Quora is a great way to keep track of content you find valuable and want to revisit later. Here\u2019s how you can save an answer:\n\n### **On the Quora Website:**\n\n1. **Find the Answer:** Navigate to the question and scroll to the answer you want to save.\n2. **Click the \"Save\" Button:** Below the answer, look for a bookmark icon or the word \"Save.\" Click it.\n3. **Choose a Collection (Optional):** After clicking \"Save,\" Quora may prompt you to save the answer to an existing collection or create a new one. Select your preferred option.\n4. **Confirm:** The answer will now be saved and can be accessed later in your \"Saved\" section.\n\n### **On the Quora Mobile App:**\n\n1. **Find the Answer:** Open the Quora app and navigate to the answer you want to save.\n2. **Tap the \"Save\" Icon:** Below the answer, tap the bookmark icon (it usually says \"Save\").\n3. **Choose a Collection (Optional):** Select an existing collection or create a new one to organize your saved content.\n4. **Confirm:** The answer is now saved and can be found in your \"Saved\" section.\n\n### **Accessing Saved Answers:**\n\n- **Website:** Click on your profile picture in the top-right corner, then select \"Saved\" from the dropdown menu.\n- **Mobile App:** Tap the profile icon in the bottom-right corner, then select \"Saved.\"\n\nYou can organize saved answers into collections for easier access and categorization.",
